{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"You know, we're going to do things a little differently."},{"time":3000,"text":"I'm not going to show you a presentation. I'm going to talk to you."},{"time":6000,"text":"And at the same time, we're going to look at just images"},{"time":11000,"text":"from a photo stream that is pretty close to live of things that --"},{"time":16000,"text":"snapshots from Second Life. So hopefully this will be fascinating."},{"time":20000,"text":"You can -- I can compete for your attention with the strange pictures"},{"time":24000,"text":"that you see on screen that come from there."},{"time":26000,"text":"I thought I'd talk a little bit about some just big ideas about this,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and then get John back out here so we can talk interactively"},{"time":35000,"text":"a little bit more and think and ask questions."},{"time":39000,"text":"You know, I guess the first question is,"},{"time":42000,"text":"why build a virtual world at all?"},{"time":47000,"text":"And I think the answer to that is always going to be"},{"time":51000,"text":"at least driven to a certain extent by the people"},{"time":53000,"text":"initially crazy enough to start the project, you know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"So I can give you a little bit of first background just on me"},{"time":61000,"text":"and what moved me as a -- really going back as far as a teenager"},{"time":66000,"text":"and then an adult, to actually try and build this kind of thing."},{"time":69000,"text":"I was a very creative kid who read a lot, and got into electronics first,"},{"time":78000,"text":"and then later, programming computers, when I was really young."},{"time":82000,"text":"I was just always trying to make things."},{"time":86000,"text":"I was just obsessed with taking things apart and building things,"},{"time":90000,"text":"and just anything I could do with my hands or with wood"},{"time":94000,"text":"or electronics or metal or anything else."},{"time":97000,"text":"And so, for example -- and it's a great Second Life thing -- I had a bedroom."},{"time":101000,"text":"And every kid, you know, as a teenager, has got his bedroom he retreats to --"},{"time":104000,"text":"but I wanted my door, I thought it would be cool if my door went up"},{"time":109000,"text":"rather than opened, like on Star Trek."},{"time":111000,"text":"I thought it would be neat to do that. And so I got up in the ceiling"},{"time":114000,"text":"and I cut through the ceiling joists, much to my parents' delight,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and put the door, you know, being pulled up through the ceiling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123000,"text":"I built -- I put a garage-door opener up in the attic"},{"time":127000,"text":"that would pull this door up."},{"time":129000,"text":"You can imagine the amount of time that it took me to do this to the house"},{"time":134000,"text":"and the displeasure of my parents."},{"time":136000,"text":"The thing that was always striking to me was that we as people"},{"time":139000,"text":"could have so many really amazing ideas about things we'd like to do,"},{"time":144000,"text":"but are so often unable, in the real world, to actually do those things --"},{"time":150000,"text":"to actually cobble together the materials"},{"time":153000,"text":"and go through the actual execution phase of building something"},{"time":156000,"text":"that you imagine from a design perspective."},{"time":158000,"text":"And so for me, I know that when the Internet came around"},{"time":161000,"text":"and I was doing computer programming and just, you know,"},{"time":164000,"text":"just generally trying to run my own little company"},{"time":167000,"text":"and figure out what to do with the Internet and with computers,"},{"time":170000,"text":"I was just immediately struck by how the ultimate thing"},{"time":176000,"text":"that you would really want to do with the Internet and with computers"},{"time":179000,"text":"would be to use the Internet and connected computers"},{"time":182000,"text":"to simulate a world to sort of recreate the laws of physics"},{"time":189000,"text":"and the rules of how things went together --"},{"time":193000,"text":"the sort of -- the idea of atoms and how to make things,"},{"time":196000,"text":"and do that inside a computer so that we could all get in there and make stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202000,"text":"And so for me that was the thing that was so enticing."},{"time":206000,"text":"I just wanted this place where you could build things."},{"time":209000,"text":"And so I think you see that in the genesis"},{"time":212000,"text":"of what has happened with Second Life, and I think it's important."},{"time":216000,"text":"I also think that more generally, the use of the Internet and technology"},{"time":222000,"text":"as a kind of a space between us for creativity and design is a general trend."},{"time":228000,"text":"It is a -- sort of a great human progress."},{"time":231000,"text":"Technology is just generally being used to allow us to create"},{"time":237000,"text":"in as shared and social a way as possible."},{"time":240000,"text":"And I think that Second Life and virtual worlds more generally"},{"time":242000,"text":"represent the best we can do to achieve that right now."},{"time":247000,"text":"You know, another way to look at that,"},{"time":249000,"text":"and related to the content and, you know, thinking about space,"},{"time":252000,"text":"is to connect sort of virtual worlds to space."},{"time":255000,"text":"I thought that might be a fun thing to talk about for a second."},{"time":258000,"text":"If you think about going into space, it's a fascinating thing."},{"time":263000,"text":"So many movies, so many kids, we all sort of"},{"time":266000,"text":"dream about exploring space. Now, why is that?"},{"time":269000,"text":"Stop for a moment and ask, why that conceit?"},{"time":271000,"text":"Why do we as people want to do that?"},{"time":275000,"text":"I think there's a couple of things. It's what we see in the movies --"},{"time":277000,"text":"you know, it's this dream that we all share."}]},{"cues":[{"time":280000,"text":"One is that if you went into space you'd be able to begin again."},{"time":285000,"text":"In some sense, you would become someone else in that journey,"},{"time":288000,"text":"because there wouldn't be -- you'd leave society and life as you know it, behind."},{"time":293000,"text":"And so inevitably, you would transform yourself --"},{"time":296000,"text":"irreversibly, in all likelihood -- as you began this exploration."},{"time":300000,"text":"And then the second thing is that there's this tangible sense"},{"time":304000,"text":"that if you travel far enough, you can find out there --"},{"time":310000,"text":"oh, yeah -- you have no idea what you're going to find"},{"time":313000,"text":"once you get there, into space."},{"time":315000,"text":"It's going to be different than here."},{"time":317000,"text":"And in fact, it's going to be so different than what we see here on earth"},{"time":322000,"text":"that anything is going to be possible."},{"time":325000,"text":"So that's kind of the idea -- we as humans crave the idea of"},{"time":328000,"text":"creating a new identity and going into a place where anything is possible."},{"time":333000,"text":"And I think that if you really sit and think about it,"},{"time":336000,"text":"virtual worlds, and where we're going"},{"time":340000,"text":"with more and more computing technology,"},{"time":344000,"text":"represent essentially the likely, really tactically possible"},{"time":350000,"text":"version of space exploration."},{"time":352000,"text":"We are moved by the idea of virtual worlds because, like space,"},{"time":357000,"text":"they allow us to reinvent ourselves and they contain anything"},{"time":361000,"text":"and everything, and probably anything could happen there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"You know, to give you a size idea about scale, you know,"},{"time":366000,"text":"comparing space to Second Life, most people don't realize, kind of --"},{"time":370000,"text":"and then this is just like the Internet in the early '90s."},{"time":373000,"text":"In fact, Second Life virtual worlds are a lot like the Internet in the early '90s today:"},{"time":376000,"text":"everybody's very excited,"},{"time":378000,"text":"there's a lot of hype and excitement about one idea or the next"},{"time":381000,"text":"from moment to moment, and then there's despair"},{"time":384000,"text":"and everybody thinks the whole thing's not going to work."},{"time":386000,"text":"Everything that's happening with Second Life"},{"time":388000,"text":"and more broadly with virtual worlds, all happened in the early '90s."},{"time":391000,"text":"We always play a game at the office where you can take any article"},{"time":394000,"text":"and find the same article where you just replace the words \"Second Life\""},{"time":398000,"text":"with \"Web,\" and \"virtual reality\" with \"Internet.\""},{"time":403000,"text":"You can find exactly the same articles"},{"time":405000,"text":"written about everything that people are observing."},{"time":409000,"text":"To give you an idea of scale, Second Life is about 20,000 CPUs at this point."},{"time":416000,"text":"It's about 20,000 computers connected together"},{"time":418000,"text":"in three facilities in the United States right now,"},{"time":422000,"text":"that are simulating this virtual space. And the virtual space itself --"},{"time":426000,"text":"there's about 250,000 people a day that are wandering around in there,"},{"time":430000,"text":"so the kind of, active population is something like a smallish city."},{"time":434000,"text":"The space itself is about 10 times the size of San Francisco,"},{"time":438000,"text":"and it's about as densely built out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"So it gives you an idea of scale. Now, it's expanding very rapidly --"},{"time":444000,"text":"about five percent a month or so right now, in terms of new servers being added."},{"time":448000,"text":"And so of course, radically unlike the real world,"},{"time":451000,"text":"and like the Internet, the whole thing is expanding"},{"time":453000,"text":"very, very quickly, and historically exponentially."},{"time":456000,"text":"So that sort of space exploration thing is matched up here"},{"time":459000,"text":"by the amount of content that's in there,"},{"time":461000,"text":"and I think that amount is critical."},{"time":463000,"text":"It was critical with the virtual world"},{"time":465000,"text":"that it be this space of truly infinite possibility."},{"time":468000,"text":"We're very sensitive to that as humans."},{"time":470000,"text":"You know, you know when you see it. You know when you can do anything in a space"},{"time":473000,"text":"and you know when you can't."},{"time":475000,"text":"Second Life today is this 20,000 machines,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and it's about 100 million or so user-created objects where, you know,"},{"time":481000,"text":"an object would be something like this, possibly interactive."},{"time":484000,"text":"Tens of millions of them are thinking all the time;"},{"time":486000,"text":"they have code attached to them."},{"time":488000,"text":"So it's a really large world already, in terms of the amount of stuff that's there"},{"time":491000,"text":"and that's very important."},{"time":493000,"text":"If anybody plays, like, World of Warcraft,"},{"time":495000,"text":"World of Warcraft comes on, like, four DVDs."},{"time":498000,"text":"Second Life, by comparison, has about 100 terabytes"},{"time":502000,"text":"of user-created data, making it about 25,000 times larger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507000,"text":"So again, like the Internet compared to AOL,"},{"time":511000,"text":"and the sort of chat rooms and content on AOL at the time,"},{"time":513000,"text":"what's happening here is something very different,"},{"time":515000,"text":"because the sheer scale of what people can do"},{"time":518000,"text":"when they're enabled to do anything they want is pretty amazing."},{"time":522000,"text":"The last big thought is that it is almost certainly true"},{"time":526000,"text":"that whatever this is going to evolve into"},{"time":529000,"text":"is going to be bigger in total usage than the Web itself."},{"time":533000,"text":"And let me justify that with two statements."},{"time":536000,"text":"Generically, what we use the Web for is to organize, exchange,"},{"time":540000,"text":"create and consume information."},{"time":542000,"text":"It's kind of like Irene talking about Google being data-driven."},{"time":546000,"text":"I'd say I kind of think about the world as being information."},{"time":549000,"text":"Everything that we interact with, all the experiences that we have,"},{"time":552000,"text":"is kind of us flowing through a sea of information"},{"time":554000,"text":"and interacting with it in different ways."},{"time":557000,"text":"The Web puts information in the form of text and images."},{"time":563000,"text":"The topology, the geography of the Web is text-to-text links for the most part."},{"time":568000,"text":"That's one way of organizing information,"},{"time":571000,"text":"but there are two things about the way you access information in a virtual world"},{"time":576000,"text":"that I think are the important ways that they're very different"},{"time":579000,"text":"and much better than what we've been able to do to date with the Web."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583000,"text":"The first is that, as I said, the --"},{"time":587000,"text":"well, the first difference for virtual worlds is that"},{"time":590000,"text":"information is presented to you in the virtual world"},{"time":593000,"text":"using the most powerful iconic symbols"},{"time":597000,"text":"that you can possibly use with human beings."},{"time":599000,"text":"So for example, C-H-A-I-R is the English word for that,"},{"time":604000,"text":"but a picture of this is a universal symbol."},{"time":609000,"text":"Everybody knows what it means. There's no need to translate it."},{"time":612000,"text":"It's also more memorable if I show you that picture,"},{"time":615000,"text":"and I show you C-H-A-I-R on a piece of paper."},{"time":617000,"text":"You can do tests that show that you'll remember"},{"time":620000,"text":"that I was talking about a chair a couple of days later a lot better."},{"time":623000,"text":"So when you organize information using the symbols of our memory,"},{"time":627000,"text":"using the most common symbols that we've been immersed in all our lives,"},{"time":631000,"text":"you maximally both excite, stimulate,"},{"time":635000,"text":"are able to remember, transfer and manipulate data."},{"time":637000,"text":"And so virtual worlds are the best way"},{"time":641000,"text":"for us to essentially organize and experience information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"And I think that's something that people have talked about for 20 years --"},{"time":648000,"text":"you know, that 3D, that lifelike environments"},{"time":652000,"text":"are really important in some magical way to us."},{"time":654000,"text":"But the second thing -- and I think this one is less obvious --"},{"time":658000,"text":"is that the experience of creating, consuming, exploring that information"},{"time":666000,"text":"is in the virtual world implicitly and inherently social."},{"time":671000,"text":"You are always there with other people."},{"time":674000,"text":"And we as humans are social creatures and must, or are aided by,"},{"time":680000,"text":"or enjoy more, the consumption of information in the presence of others."},{"time":685000,"text":"It's essential to us. You can't escape it."},{"time":688000,"text":"When you're on Amazon.com and you're looking for digital cameras or whatever,"},{"time":693000,"text":"you're on there right now, when you're on the site, with like 5,000 other people,"},{"time":699000,"text":"but you can't talk to them."},{"time":701000,"text":"You can't just turn to the people that are browsing digital cameras"},{"time":705000,"text":"on the same page as you, and ask them,"},{"time":708000,"text":"\"Hey, have you seen one of these before? Because I'm thinking about buying it.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":711000,"text":"That experience of like, shopping together, just as a simple example,"},{"time":715000,"text":"is an example of how as social creatures"},{"time":717000,"text":"we want to experience information in that way."},{"time":719000,"text":"So that second point, that we inherently experience information together"},{"time":725000,"text":"or want to experience it together,"},{"time":727000,"text":"is critical to essentially, kind of,"},{"time":730000,"text":"this trend of where we're going to use technology to connect us."},{"time":735000,"text":"And so I think, again, that it's likely that in the next decade or so"},{"time":740000,"text":"these virtual worlds are going to be the most common way as human beings"},{"time":745000,"text":"that we kind of use the electronics of the Internet, if you will,"},{"time":750000,"text":"to be together, to consume information."},{"time":754000,"text":"You know, mapping in India -- that's such a great example."},{"time":756000,"text":"Maybe the solution there involves talking to other people in real time."},{"time":761000,"text":"Asking for advice, rather than any possible way"},{"time":766000,"text":"that you could just statically organize a map."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"So I think that's another big point."},{"time":772000,"text":"I think that wherever this is all going,"},{"time":774000,"text":"whether it's Second Life or its descendants, or something broader"},{"time":779000,"text":"that happens all around the world at a lot of different points --"},{"time":782000,"text":"this is what we're going to see the Internet used for,"},{"time":785000,"text":"and total traffic and total unique users is going to invert,"},{"time":789000,"text":"so that the Web and its bibliographic set of text and graphical information"},{"time":794000,"text":"is going to become a tool or a part of that consumption pattern,"},{"time":797000,"text":"but the pattern itself is going to happen mostly in this type of an environment."},{"time":801000,"text":"Big idea, but I think highly defensible."},{"time":805000,"text":"So let me stop there and bring John back,"},{"time":808000,"text":"and maybe we can just have a longer conversation."},{"time":811000,"text":"Thank you. John. That's great."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":818000,"text":"John Hockenberry: Why is the creation, the impulse to create Second Life,"},{"time":822000,"text":"not a utopian impulse?"},{"time":825000,"text":"Like for example, in the 19th century,"},{"time":827000,"text":"any number of works of literature that imagined alternative worlds"},{"time":831000,"text":"were explicitly utopian."}]},{"cues":[{"time":833000,"text":"Philip Rosedale: I think that's great. That's such a deep question. Yeah."},{"time":837000,"text":"Is a virtual world likely to be a utopia, would be one way I'd say it."},{"time":842000,"text":"The answer is no, and I think the reason why is because"},{"time":846000,"text":"the Web itself as a good example is profoundly bottoms-up."},{"time":849000,"text":"That idea of infinite possibility, that magic of anything can happen,"},{"time":854000,"text":"only happens in an environment"},{"time":856000,"text":"where you really know that there's a fundamental freedom"},{"time":859000,"text":"at the level of the individual actor, at the level of the Lego blocks,"},{"time":863000,"text":"if you will, that make up the virtual world."},{"time":865000,"text":"You have to have that level of freedom, and so I'm often asked that,"},{"time":868000,"text":"you know, is there a, kind of, utopian or,"},{"time":870000,"text":"is there a utopian tendency to Second Life and things like it,"},{"time":873000,"text":"that you would create a world that has a grand scheme to it?"},{"time":876000,"text":"Those top-down schemes are alienating to just about everybody,"},{"time":880000,"text":"even if you mean well when you build them."},{"time":883000,"text":"And what's more, human society, when it's controlled,"},{"time":887000,"text":"when you set out a grand scheme of rules,"},{"time":889000,"text":"a new way of people interacting, or a new way of laying out a city, or whatever,"},{"time":893000,"text":"that stuff historically has never scaled much beyond,"},{"time":896000,"text":"you know -- I always laughingly say -- the Mall of America, you know,"},{"time":899000,"text":"which is like, the largest piece of centrally designed architecture"},{"time":902000,"text":"that, you know, has been built."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"JH: The Kremlin was pretty big."}]},{"cues":[{"time":906000,"text":"PR: The Kremlin, yeah. That's true. The whole complex."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909000,"text":"JH: Give me a story of a tool you created at the beginning"},{"time":913000,"text":"in Second Life that you were pretty sure people would want to use"},{"time":916000,"text":"in the creation of their avatars or in communicating"},{"time":919000,"text":"that people actually in practice said, no, I'm not interested in that at all,"},{"time":923000,"text":"and name something that you didn't come up with"},{"time":928000,"text":"that almost immediately people began to demand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931000,"text":"PR: I'm sure I can think of multiple examples of both of those."},{"time":934000,"text":"One of my favorites. I had this feature that I built into Second Life --"},{"time":937000,"text":"I was really passionate about it."},{"time":939000,"text":"It was an ability to kind of walk up close to somebody"},{"time":942000,"text":"and have a more private conversation,"},{"time":944000,"text":"but it wasn't instant messaging because you had to sort of befriend somebody."},{"time":947000,"text":"It was just this idea that you could kind of have a private chat."},{"time":950000,"text":"I just remember it was one of those examples of data-driven design."},{"time":953000,"text":"I thought it was such a good idea from my perspective,"},{"time":955000,"text":"and it was just absolutely never used, and we ultimately --"},{"time":958000,"text":"I think we've now turned it off, if I remember."},{"time":960000,"text":"We finally gave up, took it out of the code."},{"time":963000,"text":"But more generally, you know, one other example I think about this,"},{"time":967000,"text":"which is great relative to the utopian idea."},{"time":970000,"text":"Second Life originally had 16 simulators. It now has 20,000."}]},{"cues":[{"time":975000,"text":"So when it only had 16,"},{"time":977000,"text":"it was only about as big as this college campus."},{"time":980000,"text":"And we had -- we zoned it, you know: we put a nightclub,"},{"time":984000,"text":"we put a disco where you could dance,"},{"time":986000,"text":"and then we had a place where you could fight with guns if you wanted to,"},{"time":990000,"text":"and we had another place that was like a boardwalk, kind of a Coney Island."},{"time":994000,"text":"And we laid out the zoning, but of course,"},{"time":997000,"text":"people could build all around it however they wanted to."},{"time":1000000,"text":"And what was so amazing right from the start was that the idea"},{"time":1004000,"text":"that we had put out in the zoning concept, basically,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"was instantly and thoroughly ignored,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"and like, two months into the whole thing,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"-- which is really a small amount of time, even in Second Life time --"},{"time":1016000,"text":"I remember the users, the people who were then using Second Life,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"the residents came to me and said, we want to buy the disco --"},{"time":1024000,"text":"because I had built it -- we want to buy that land and raze it"},{"time":1028000,"text":"and put houses on it. And I sold it to them --"},{"time":1031000,"text":"I mean, we transferred ownership and they had a big party"},{"time":1033000,"text":"and blew up the entire building."},{"time":1035000,"text":"And I remember that that was just so telling, you know,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"that you didn't know exactly what was going to happen."},{"time":1041000,"text":"When you think about stuff that people have built that's popular --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044000,"text":"JH: CBGB's has to close eventually, you know. That's the rule."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1047000,"text":"PR: Exactly. And it -- but it closed on day one, basically, in Internet time."},{"time":1053000,"text":"You know, an example of something -- pregnancy."},{"time":1056000,"text":"You can have a baby in Second Life."},{"time":1059000,"text":"This is done entirely using, kind of, the tools that are built into Second Life,"},{"time":1065000,"text":"so the innate concept of becoming pregnant and having a baby, of course --"},{"time":1069000,"text":"Second Life is, at the platform level, at the level of the company -- at Linden Lab --"},{"time":1074000,"text":"Second Life has no game properties to it whatsoever."},{"time":1077000,"text":"There is no attempt to structure the experience,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"to make it utopian in that sense that we put into it."},{"time":1082000,"text":"So of course, we never would have put a mechanism for having babies or, you know,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"taking two avatars and merging them, or something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1088000,"text":"But people built the ability to have babies and care for babies"},{"time":1093000,"text":"as a purchasable experience that you can have in Second Life and so --"},{"time":1097000,"text":"I mean, that's a pretty fascinating example of, you know,"},{"time":1100000,"text":"what goes on in the overall economy."},{"time":1102000,"text":"And of course, the existence of an economy is another idea."},{"time":1104000,"text":"I didn't talk about it, but it's a critical feature."},{"time":1107000,"text":"When people are given the opportunity to create in the world,"},{"time":1110000,"text":"there's really two things they want."},{"time":1112000,"text":"One is fair ownership of the things they create."},{"time":1115000,"text":"And then the second one is -- if they feel like it,"},{"time":1117000,"text":"and they're not going to do it in every case, but in many they are --"},{"time":1119000,"text":"they want to actually be able to sell that creation"},{"time":1123000,"text":"as a way of providing for their own livelihood."},{"time":1125000,"text":"True on the Web -- also true in Second Life."},{"time":1128000,"text":"And so the existence of an economy is critical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"JH: Questions for Philip Rosedale? Right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"(Audience: Well, first an observation, which is that you look like a character.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1137000,"text":"JH: The observation is, Philip has been accused of looking like a character,"},{"time":1142000,"text":"an avatar, in Second Life."},{"time":1144000,"text":"Respond, and then we'll get the rest of your question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146000,"text":"PR: But I don't look like my avatar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1148000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1150000,"text":"How many people here know what my avatar looks like?"},{"time":1152000,"text":"That's probably not very many."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154000,"text":"JH: Are you ripping off somebody else's avatar with that, sort of --\n"},{"time":1156000,"text":"PR: No, no. I didn't. One of the other guys at work had a fantastic avatar --"},{"time":1159000,"text":"a female avatar -- that I used to be once in a while."},{"time":1162000,"text":"But my avatar is a guy wearing chaps."},{"time":1169000,"text":"Spiky hair -- spikier than this. Kind of orange hair."},{"time":1172000,"text":"Handlebar mustache. Kind of a Village People sort of a character."},{"time":1177000,"text":"So, very cool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1179000,"text":"JH: And your question?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1181000,"text":"(Audience: [Unclear].)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184000,"text":"JH: The question is, there appears to be a lack of cultural fine-tuning in Second Life."},{"time":1190000,"text":"It doesn't seem to have its own culture,"},{"time":1192000,"text":"and the sort of differences that exist in the real world"},{"time":1194000,"text":"aren't translated into the Second Life map."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1197000,"text":"PR: Well, first of all, we're very early,"},{"time":1199000,"text":"so this has only been going on for a few years."},{"time":1202000,"text":"And so part of what we see is the same evolution of human behavior"},{"time":1205000,"text":"that you see in emerging societies."},{"time":1207000,"text":"So a fair criticism -- is what it is -- of Second Life today is that"},{"time":1211000,"text":"it's more like the Wild West than it is like Rome, from a cultural standpoint."},{"time":1216000,"text":"That said, the evolution of, and the nuanced interaction that creates culture,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"is happening at 10 times the speed of the real world,"},{"time":1225000,"text":"and in an environment where, if you walk into a bar in Second Life,"},{"time":1230000,"text":"65 percent of the people there are not in the United States,"},{"time":1233000,"text":"and in fact are speaking their, you know, various and different languages."},{"time":1238000,"text":"In fact, one of the ways to make money in Second Life"},{"time":1240000,"text":"is to make really cool translators that you drag onto your body"},{"time":1245000,"text":"and they basically, kind of, pop up on your screen"},{"time":1247000,"text":"and allow you to use Google or Babel Fish"},{"time":1250000,"text":"or one of the other online text translators to on-the-fly"},{"time":1253000,"text":"translate spoken -- I'm sorry -- typed text between individuals."},{"time":1258000,"text":"And so, the multicultural nature and the sort of cultural melting pot"},{"time":1262000,"text":"that's happening inside Second Life is quite --"},{"time":1265000,"text":"I think, quite remarkable relative to what in real human terms"},{"time":1270000,"text":"in the real world we've ever been able to achieve."},{"time":1272000,"text":"So, I think that culture will fine-tune, it will emerge,"},{"time":1275000,"text":"but we still have some years to wait while that happens,"},{"time":1279000,"text":"as you would naturally expect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1281000,"text":"JH: Other questions? Right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1284000,"text":"(Audience: What's your demographic?)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1286000,"text":"JH: What's your demographic?"},{"time":1288000,"text":"PR: So, the question is, what's the demographic."},{"time":1290000,"text":"So, the average age of a person in Second Life is 32,"},{"time":1295000,"text":"however, the use of Second Life increases dramatically"},{"time":1300000,"text":"as your physical age increases. So as you go from age 30 to age 60 --"},{"time":1305000,"text":"and there are many people in their sixties using Second Life --"},{"time":1307000,"text":"this is also not a sharp curve -- it's very, very distributed --"},{"time":1312000,"text":"usage goes up in terms of, like, hours per week by 40 percent"},{"time":1316000,"text":"as you go from age 30 to age 60 in real life, so there's not --"},{"time":1320000,"text":"many people make the mistake of believing that Second Life"},{"time":1322000,"text":"is some kind of an online game. Actually it's generally unappealing --"},{"time":1327000,"text":"I'm just speaking broadly and critically --"},{"time":1330000,"text":"it's not very appealing to people that play online video games,"},{"time":1332000,"text":"because the graphics are not yet equivalent to --"},{"time":1336000,"text":"I mean, these are very nice pictures,"},{"time":1337000,"text":"but in general the graphics are not quite equivalent"},{"time":1339000,"text":"to the fine-tuned graphics that you see in a Grand Theft Auto 4."},{"time":1343000,"text":"So average age: 32. I mentioned"},{"time":1346000,"text":"65 percent of the users are not in the United States."},{"time":1348000,"text":"The distribution amongst countries is extremely broad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1351000,"text":"There's users from, you know, virtually every country in the world now in Second Life."},{"time":1354000,"text":"The dominant ones are -- if you take the UK and Europe,"},{"time":1358000,"text":"together they make up about 55 percent of the usage base in Second Life."},{"time":1362000,"text":"In terms of psychographic --"},{"time":1364000,"text":"oh, men and women: men and women are almost equally matched in Second Life,"},{"time":1369000,"text":"so about 45 percent of the people online right now on Second Life are women."},{"time":1374000,"text":"Women use Second Life, though,"},{"time":1376000,"text":"about 30 to 40 percent more, on an hours basis, than men do,"},{"time":1379000,"text":"meaning that more men sign up than women,"},{"time":1381000,"text":"and more women stay and use it than men."},{"time":1384000,"text":"So that's another demographic fact."},{"time":1386000,"text":"In terms of psychographic, you know, the people in Second Life"},{"time":1391000,"text":"are remarkably dissimilar relative to what you might think,"},{"time":1395000,"text":"when you go in and talk to them and meet them, and I would, you know,"},{"time":1397000,"text":"challenge you to just do this and find out."},{"time":1399000,"text":"But it's not a bunch of programmers."},{"time":1402000,"text":"It's not easy to describe as a demographic."},{"time":1406000,"text":"If I had to just sort of paint a broad picture, I'd say, remember the people"},{"time":1410000,"text":"who were really getting into eBay in the first few years of eBay?"},{"time":1414000,"text":"Maybe a little bit like that: in other words, people who are early adopters."},{"time":1417000,"text":"They tend to be creative. They tend to be entrepreneurial."},{"time":1420000,"text":"A lot of them -- about 55,000 people so far -- are cash-flow positive:"},{"time":1424000,"text":"they're making money from what -- I mean, real-world money --"},{"time":1427000,"text":"from what they're doing in Second Life, so it's a very build --"},{"time":1431000,"text":"still a creative, building things, build-your-own-business"},{"time":1434000,"text":"type of an orientation. So, that's it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1436000,"text":"JH: You describe yourself, Philip, as someone who was really creative"},{"time":1438000,"text":"when you were young and, you know, liked to make things."},{"time":1442000,"text":"I mean, it's not often that you hear somebody"},{"time":1445000,"text":"describe themselves as really creative."},{"time":1447000,"text":"I suspect that's possibly a euphemism for C student"},{"time":1451000,"text":"who spent a lot of time in his room? Is it possible?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1454000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1455000,"text":"PR: I was a -- there were times I was a C student. You know, it's funny."},{"time":1459000,"text":"When I got to college -- I studied physics in college --"},{"time":1461000,"text":"and I got really -- it was funny,"},{"time":1463000,"text":"because I was definitely a more antisocial kid. I read all the time."},{"time":1468000,"text":"I was shy. I don't seem like it now, but I was very shy."},{"time":1473000,"text":"Moved around a bunch -- had that experience too."},{"time":1475000,"text":"So I did, kind of, I think, live in my own world,"},{"time":1478000,"text":"and obviously that helps, you know, engage your real interest in something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1481000,"text":"JH: So you're on your fifth life at this point?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1484000,"text":"PR: If you count, yeah, cities. So -- but I did --"},{"time":1490000,"text":"and I didn't do -- I think I didn't do as well in school as I could have. I think you're right."},{"time":1494000,"text":"I wasn't, like, an obsessed -- you know, get A's kind of guy."},{"time":1498000,"text":"I was going to say, I had a great social experience"},{"time":1500000,"text":"when I went to college that I hadn't had before,"},{"time":1502000,"text":"a more fraternal experience, where I met six or seven other guys"},{"time":1505000,"text":"who I studied physics with, and I was very competitive with them,"},{"time":1508000,"text":"so then I started to get A's. But you're right: I wasn't an A student."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1512000,"text":"JH: Last question. Right here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1514000,"text":"(Audience: In the pamphlet, there's a statement -- )"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1517000,"text":"JH: You want to paraphrase that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1519000,"text":"PR: Yeah, so let me restate that."},{"time":1521000,"text":"So, you're saying that in the pamphlet there's a statement"},{"time":1524000,"text":"that we may come to prefer our digital selves to our real ones --"},{"time":1528000,"text":"our more malleable or manageable digital identities to our real identities --"},{"time":1532000,"text":"and that in fact, much of human life and human experience"},{"time":1535000,"text":"may move into the digital realm."},{"time":1538000,"text":"And then that's kind of a horrifying thought, of course."},{"time":1541000,"text":"That's a frightening change, frightening disruption."},{"time":1545000,"text":"I guess, and you're asking, what do I think about that? How do I --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1548000,"text":"JH: What's your response to the people who would say, that's horrifying?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1550000,"text":"(Audience: If someone would say to you, I find that disturbing,"},{"time":1552000,"text":"what would be your response?)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1554000,"text":"PR: Well, I'd say a couple of things."},{"time":1557000,"text":"One is, it's disturbing like the Internet or electricity was."},{"time":1560000,"text":"That is to say, it's a big change, but it isn't avoidable."},{"time":1564000,"text":"So, no amount of backpedaling or intentional behavior"},{"time":1569000,"text":"or political behavior is going to keep these technology changes"},{"time":1572000,"text":"from connecting us together,"},{"time":1574000,"text":"because the basic motive that people have --"},{"time":1576000,"text":"to be creative and entrepreneurial -- is going to drive energy"},{"time":1580000,"text":"into these virtual worlds in the same way that it has with the Web."},{"time":1583000,"text":"So this change, I believe, is a huge disruptive change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1588000,"text":"Obviously, I'm the optimist and a big believer in what's going on here,"},{"time":1592000,"text":"but I think that as -- even a sober, you know, the most sober,"},{"time":1596000,"text":"disconnected thinker about this, looking at it from the side,"},{"time":1599000,"text":"has to conclude, based on the data,"},{"time":1601000,"text":"that with those kinds of economic forces at play,"},{"time":1603000,"text":"there is definitely going to be a sea change,"},{"time":1606000,"text":"and that change is going to be intensely disruptive"},{"time":1609000,"text":"relative to our concept of our very lives and being,"},{"time":1613000,"text":"and our identities, as well."},{"time":1615000,"text":"I don't think we can get away from those changes."},{"time":1617000,"text":"I think generally, we were talking about this --"},{"time":1620000,"text":"I think that generally being present in a virtual world and being challenged by it,"},{"time":1626000,"text":"being -- surviving there, having a good life there, so to speak,"},{"time":1630000,"text":"is a challenge because of the multiculturality of it,"},{"time":1633000,"text":"because of the languages, because of the entrepreneurial richness of it,"},{"time":1638000,"text":"the sort of flea market nature, if you will, of the virtual world today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1641000,"text":"It puts challenges on us to rise to. We must be better than ourselves, in many ways."},{"time":1647000,"text":"We must learn things and, you know, be more tolerant,"},{"time":1650000,"text":"and be smarter and learn faster and be more creative, perhaps,"},{"time":1656000,"text":"than we are typically in our real lives."},{"time":1658000,"text":"And I think that if that is true of virtual worlds,"},{"time":1660000,"text":"then these changes, though scary -- and, I say, inevitable --"},{"time":1664000,"text":"are ultimately for the better,"},{"time":1666000,"text":"and therefore something that we should ride out."},{"time":1669000,"text":"But I would say that -- and many other authors and speakers about this,"},{"time":1673000,"text":"other than me, have said, you know, fasten your seat belts"},{"time":1676000,"text":"because the change is coming. There are going to be big changes."},{"time":1679000,"text":"JH: Philip Rosedale, thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1681000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}